ply. This book proposes an atonement that could again bring people and prairie together.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGrassland ecologyxManitobaxSte. Madeleine. 0aGrassland ecologyzManitobazSte. Madeleine. 0aIndigenous peopleszCanada. 0aMétisxLand tenurezManitobazSte. MadeleinexHistory. 0aMétiszManitobazSte. MadeleinexHistory. 0aMétisxHistoryxManitobaxSte. Madeleine. 0aMétisxLand tenurexHistoryxManitobaxSte. Madeleine. 0aMétisxLand tenurezManitobazSte. MadeleinexHistory. 0aMétiszManitobazSte. MadeleinexHistory. 7aNATURE / Ecosystems & Habitats / Plains & Prairies.2bisacsh  aMetis.  apasture land.  areconciliation.1 aFleury, Norman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311127380808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016z978311127630440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088977455140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889774551423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889774551/original  a978-3-11-127380-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-127630-4  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles